ğŸ§  What is Conditional Rendering?

**Conditional Rendering** means showing different UI based on a condition.

ğŸ“Œ Example:

* If user logged in â†’ Show Dashboard
* If not logged in â†’ Show Login button

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 1ï¸âƒ£ Using if-else Statement

```jsx
function Greeting({ isLoggedIn }) {
  if (isLoggedIn) {
    return <h2>Welcome Back!</h2>;
  } else {
    return <h2>Please Login</h2>;
  }
}
```

âœ” Clear
âœ” Best for large logic

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 2ï¸âƒ£ Using Ternary Operator (Most Used â­)

```jsx
function Greeting({ isLoggedIn }) {
  return (
    <h2>
      {isLoggedIn ? "Welcome Back!" : "Please Login"}
    </h2>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Syntax:

```
condition ? truePart : falsePart
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 3ï¸âƒ£ Using Logical AND (&&)

Used when you only want to show something if condition is true.

```jsx
{isLoggedIn && <Dashboard />}
```

ğŸ“Œ If false â†’ nothing renders

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 4ï¸âƒ£ Conditional Rendering with State

```jsx
import { useState } from "react";

function Toggle() {
  const [show, setShow] = useState(false);

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={() => setShow(!show)}>
        Toggle
      </button>

      {show && <p>This is visible</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ State controls UI

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 5ï¸âƒ£ Rendering Multiple Conditions

```jsx
function Status({ status }) {
  return (
    <div>
      {status === "loading" && <p>Loading...</p>}
      {status === "success" && <p>Success!</p>}
      {status === "error" && <p>Error occurred</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 6ï¸âƒ£ Conditional Rendering with Variables

```jsx
let message;

if (isLoggedIn) {
  message = <h2>Welcome</h2>;
} else {
  message = <h2>Login</h2>;
}

return <div>{message}</div>;
```

âœ” Cleaner for complex UI

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 7ï¸âƒ£ Rendering Lists Conditionally

```jsx
{items.length > 0 ? (
  items.map(item => <li key={item.id}>{item.name}</li>)
) : (
  <p>No Items Found</p>
)}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Best Method When?

| Situation        | Use                      |
| ---------------- | ------------------------ |
| Simple condition | `&&`                     |
| Two outcomes     | Ternary                  |
| Complex logic    | if-else                  |
| Multiple states  | Switch / multiple checks |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âš ï¸ Common Mistakes

âŒ Writing large ternary expressions
âŒ Forgetting `key` in lists
âŒ Using `&&` when false might show 0
âŒ Overcomplicating UI logic

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices

âœ” Keep conditions simple
âœ” Avoid nested ternaries
âœ” Extract complex logic into functions
âœ” Use meaningful state names
âœ” Keep UI readable

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Real-World Use Cases

* Login / Logout button
* Show loading spinner
* Display error message
* Toggle dark mode
* Show/hide modal
* Role-based dashboard

